according to seven central narratives: subtraction, renewal, transsecular, postnaturalist, construct, perennial, and developmental. Examining the basic logic, insights, and limitations of each of these narratives, Schewel ranges from Martin Heidegger to Muhammad Iqbal, from Daniel Dennett to Charles Taylor, to offer an incisive, broad, and original perspective on religion in the modern world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Feb 2020) 0aReligionxHistoriography. 0aReligionxPhilosophy. 7aRELIGION / History.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYUP eBook Package 2017z978311063898140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300231410423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780300231410.jpg  a978-3-11-063898-1  YUP eBook Package 2017b2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles